<br>
Second, other places you may consider going for exp at level 51 is LOY, Trakanon's Teeth and the drolvargs in Dreadlands.<br>
<br>
Third, all of you wizards who think that a 51 wizard should know how to kite by 51 or switch classes are idiots.  Just because a wizard doesn't kite at an early age does not mean they aren't good wizards or happy with their class.  It generally means that they are social and like groups.  I just learned to kite at level 52 and I would never reconsider my choice of being a wizard and I find it offensive that you think I should.  I enjoy groups and have friends to play with.<br>
<br>
Fourth, Cobalt Scar is still overcamped in my opinion.  I'm there now because I need arctic wyvern hides for my tailoring and the experience isn't bad.  I absolutely HATE people who kite ALL the wyverns at one time and leave none for anyone else or pull from wherever they want.  That's just plain rude.  I try to just pull the same 8 (generally 4 at a time although I'm sure I could do all 8 at once) and let others have some wyverns too but people are constantly coming over and pulling the ones I'm working on or taking all of them at one time.  I do not kill the otters because I'm also a brewer and buy from the one down there. <p>Renia - wizardess of Cazic-Thule<br>
